Send Links in Messaging Sessions

To share a link with a customer, send an enhanced link messaging component or copy and paste the URL into the messaging field. Required editions: Lightning Experience.

This article applies to: Messaging for In-App, Web, standard and enhanced WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, SMS, Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

User permissions needed:
Messaging for In-App and Web permission set license
Messaging for In-App and Web user permission
Messaging Agent

In enhanced WhatsApp channels, use the copy and paste method. To send a URL in WhatsApp, auto-generated link previews are typically created.

Send an enhanced link messaging component or copy and paste the URL into the messaging field.
See Also: Send Messaging Components in Messaging Sessions
Create and Send Enhanced Links in Messaging Sessions
title: Sending Links in Service Cloud Messaging
